hits.description: Contains the configuration for all regulatory exams. Regulatory exams are multiple choice exams that can be associated with a process and require a pass before allowing an applicant to proceed. The exam can have a fee required, any number of questions and sections within the exam. Parameters include the number of questions displayed per page, the pass rate of the exam, maximum attempts allowed before intervention is required, time limit in minutes, the number of days the exam is valid for and would not be required to be retaken, if the exam is active, and the associated process(s) this exam will appear in. Regulatory exams can be added with no system impact on initial system configuration.

pay_is_acceptable.description:
- Select ?Yes? to indicate that this is an acceptable payment method at checkout. It is not an acceptable payment method at checkout when set to ?No? or ?Unset?.

Payment methods are configurable. The acceptable payment methods are:
 - Check (standard & offline)
 - Credit Card (standard & online)
 - e-Check (standard & offline)
 - Employer Pay
 - Interac E-Transfer
 - Money Order (standard & offline)
 - Pay by another organization
 - Prepaid Account
 - Wire Transfer

pay_is_offline_payment.description:
Select ?Yes? to indicate that this payment method is offline at checkout. It is offline at checkout when set to ?No? or ?Unset?.

Offline payments are payments sent via check and these checks must be manually processed. An invoice record is created with a status of ?balance owing? for each offline payment per account. Open an invoice, click on the Pay Invoice button, select and enter the payment details as prompted on the Process Payment form that appears, and then click on Proceed to complete processing the payment.
